@startuml sequence

skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 20
skinparam BoxPadding 10
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFFCC
skinparam NoteBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam SequenceGroupBodyBackgroundColor #F5F5FF
scale 1.5

autonumber
actor Client
boundary Gateway
participant "Reservation Service" as Reservation
queue "Kafka: reservation-service.reservation-created" as KafkaReservation
participant "Payment Service" as Payment
queue "Kafka: payment-service.payment-confirmed" as KafkaPaymentConfirmed
queue "Kafka: payment-service.payment-failed" as KafkaPaymentFailed
participant "Notification Service" as Notification

== Create Reservation (synchronous HTTP) ==

Client -> Gateway: POST /api/reservations
activate Gateway
Gateway -> Reservation: Create Reservation Request
activate Reservation
Reservation -> Reservation: @Transactional:\n  1. Save Reservation (status: CREATED)\n  2. Save OutboxEvent (ReservationCreatedEvent, status: NEW)
Reservation --> Gateway: Reservation Created Response (id, status=CREATED)
deactivate Reservation
Gateway --> Client: HTTP 201 Created
deactivate Gateway

note over Client, Notification
  Client receives immediate HTTP response.
  Async processing continues in background (0–5s per hop).
end note

== Outbox Scheduler (~every 5s) publishes event ==

Reservation -> KafkaReservation: Publish ReservationCreatedEvent\n(OutboxEvent marked SENT)
activate KafkaReservation

== Payment Processing (async) ==

KafkaReservation -> Payment: Consume ReservationCreatedEvent\n(consumer group: payment-service-group)
activate Payment
Payment -> Payment: @Transactional:\n  1. Save Payment (status: CREATED)\n  2. Save OutboxEvent (status: NEW)
deactivate KafkaReservation

alt Payment Successful (manual confirm via API)
    Payment -> Payment: @Transactional:\n  1. Update Payment (status: CONFIRMED)\n  2. Save OutboxEvent (PaymentConfirmedEvent, status: NEW)
    Payment -> KafkaPaymentConfirmed: Publish PaymentConfirmedEvent\n(OutboxEvent marked SENT)
    activate KafkaPaymentConfirmed

    KafkaPaymentConfirmed -> Notification: Consume PaymentConfirmedEvent\n(notification-service-group)
    activate Notification
    Notification -> Notification: Insert notification_log
    deactivate Notification

    KafkaPaymentConfirmed -> Reservation: Consume PaymentConfirmedEvent\n(reservation-service-group)
    activate Reservation
    Reservation -> Reservation: Update Reservation status: PAID
    deactivate Reservation
    deactivate KafkaPaymentConfirmed

else Payment Failed
    Payment -> Payment: @Transactional:\n  1. Update Payment (status: FAILED)\n  2. Save OutboxEvent (PaymentFailedEvent, status: NEW)
    Payment -> KafkaPaymentFailed: Publish PaymentFailedEvent\n(OutboxEvent marked SENT)
    activate KafkaPaymentFailed

    KafkaPaymentFailed -> Notification: Consume PaymentFailedEvent\n(notification-service-group)
    activate Notification
    Notification -> Notification: Insert notification_log
    deactivate Notification

    KafkaPaymentFailed -> Reservation: Consume PaymentFailedEvent\n(reservation-service-group)
    activate Reservation
    Reservation -> Reservation: Update Reservation status: PAYMENT_FAILED
    deactivate Reservation
    deactivate KafkaPaymentFailed
end
deactivate Payment

note over Client, Notification
  Full E2E time: 4.7–10.3s (median 5.21s)
  due to 2x Outbox scheduler jitter (0–5s each hop).
  Bimodal distribution caused by fixedDelay=5000ms.
end note

@enduml
